<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1163724042242">
<term>cylindrical coordinate system</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163724042248">a way to describe a location in space with an ordered triple <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> where <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> represents the polar coordinates of the point’s projection in the <emphasis effect="italics">xy</emphasis>-plane, and <m:math><m:mi>z</m:mi></m:math> represents the point’s projection onto the <emphasis effect="italics">z</emphasis>-axis</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1163723290017">
<term>spherical coordinate system</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163723290022">a way to describe a location in space with an ordered triple <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>ρ</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>φ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> where <m:math><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:math> is the distance between <m:math><m:mi>P</m:mi></m:math> and the origin <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>ρ</m:mi><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> <m:math><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:math> is the same angle used to describe the location in cylindrical coordinates, and <m:math><m:mi>φ</m:mi></m:math> is the angle formed by the positive <emphasis effect="italics">z</emphasis>-axis and line segment <m:math><m:mrow><m:mover accent="true"><m:mrow><m:mi>O</m:mi><m:mi>P</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="true">—</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> where <m:math><m:mi>O</m:mi></m:math> is the origin and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>≤</m:mo><m:mi>φ</m:mi><m:mo>≤</m:mo><m:mi>π</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
